						               													<description>A roll-and-move game that aims at teaching children how to safely get to school (traffic rules).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game consists of a game board, 4 player pieces, 16 cards, 60 plastic chips, a number die and a colour die. The board shows a path to school.  The aim of the game is decided by the players - either being first to reach school or winning the most chips.&amp;#10;Players take turns rolling the number die and move their piece according to the die roll. If you land on a space with a circle next to it, you earn a chip. Reaching a stop sign means you have to stop. On your next turn, you roll the colour die and can move on if you roll green. Landing on a space with an exclamation mark means you've put yourself in danger (board shows a dangerous situation) and you lose a chip.&amp;#10;There is also a variant that uses cards: Before crossing a road, you have to answer a road safety question printed on one of the cards.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
